        <div class="secondary-content t-border masa">
        <div class="playa">
        <img src="http://i2.wp.com/www.paglaomhostel.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/sugbalagoon.jpg?resize=640%2C320" alt="Lagoon">
      <h3>Activities Available</h3>
      <p>
        Siargao Island, also called the surfing capital of the Philippines is located on the southeast coast, facing the Pacific Ocean. The tear-drop shaped island offers white uncrowded beaches, endless of coconut fields and a very unique local vibe. Here you can be adventurous, lazy and stoked, Siargao has something for everyone. 
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="http://i1.wp.com/www.paglaomhostel.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/10698_273236272885441_232063243792394972_n.jpg?resize=640%2C320">"SURF"--
Play surf in the 8th best surf-spots in the world. Good for beginners up to pros.</a></li>
        <li><a href="http://i2.wp.com/www.paglaomhostel.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/sugbalagoon.jpg?resize=640%2C320">"CAUB"--
Enjoy and relax at Sugba Lagoon after you travelled through the second largest mangroove reserve in the country.</a></li>
        <li><a href="http://i2.wp.com/www.paglaomhostel.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/sohotoncave.jpg?resize=635%2C320">"SOHOTON CAVES"--
Explore different caves and play with jelly fish on this adventurous trip.</a></li>
      </ul>
       </div>
       
       <div class="piscina">	
       <img src="http://i1.wp.com/www.paglaomhostel.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/mam-onbeach.jpg?resize=640%2C320" alt="Turquoise water">		
      <h3>More Activities</h3>
      <p>
        There are more activities out there... so get ready to bring your "A" game.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="http://i2.wp.com/www.paglaomhostel.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/landtours.jpg?resize=640%2C320">"LANDTRIPS"--
Plunge into a one of a kind rock pool formation or enjoy a serene waterfall.</a></li>
        <li><a href="http://i1.wp.com/www.paglaomhostel.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/mam-onbeach.jpg?resize=640%2C320">"MAM-ON ISLAND"--
Visit the marvelous island & snorkel in turquoise water by the beach.</a></li>
        <li><a href="http://i2.wp.com/www.paglaomhostel.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/dineandrink.jpg?resize=640%2C320">"DINE & DRINK"--
